<sn><md>### Table of Syllabus for **Microbiology of Soil and Environment (SES 203)**  

| **Topic**                                                                 | **Subtopics**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Historical Development and Scope**                                      | - Branches and scope of environmental microbiology.<br>- Applications in soil, agriculture, food, and industry.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| **Protist Concept and Classification**                                    | - Eukaryotic vs. prokaryotic protists.<br>- Whittaker’s Five Kingdom concept.<br>- Characteristics, classification, morphology, growth, and reproduction of bacteria, fungi, and algae.<br>- Principles and types of microscopes.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| **Soil Microbial Communities**                                            | - Soil as a source of energy and nutrients (minerals, organic matter, biomass).<br>- Soil as a medium for microbial growth.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| **Microbial Distribution and Survival**                                   | - Origin, survival, and distribution of microorganisms in soil, water, and air.<br>- Factors affecting microbial growth and abundance.<br>- Microbiology of freshwater, polluted water, brackish water, hot water, submerged soils, arid regions, and polar regions.<br>- Microorganisms in extreme environments.                                                                                                                                                             |
| **Biogeochemical Cycles**                                                 | - Role of microorganisms in carbon, nitrogen, sulfur, and phosphorus cycles.<br>- Microorganisms in the food chain.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
| **Aquatic Microbiology and Sewage Treatment**                             | - Aquatic microorganisms and water quality.<br>- Role in water treatment and sewage (wastewater) treatment.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| **Microbial Interactions**                                                | - Mutualism, commensalism, antagonism, competition, parasitism, predation.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| **Enzymes and Metabolism**                                                | - Types and mode of action of enzymes.<br>- Factors affecting enzyme activity.<br>- Microbial metabolism: oxidative and fermentation pathways.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| **Recommended Books**                                                     | - *Ecology* – Ken Killham<br>- *Principles of Microbiology* – Ronald M. Atlas<br>- *Environmental Microbiology* – R.M. Maier et al.<br>- *Fundamentals of Microbiology* – Edward Alcamo<br>- *Microbiology* – Pelczar et al.<br>- *General Microbiology* – Stainer et al.<br>- *Introduction to Microbiology* – Walter, McBee, and Temple<br>- *Introduction to Soil Microbiology* – Martin Alexander.                                                                         |

**Credit:** 2  
